    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework demonstrates sufficient credibility for the stated COU. All three primary QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) across the full ensemble of three independent FEA models. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test Conditions (achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is acknowledged; the credibility claim is accordingly scoped to the single tested ASTM F1717 configuration. The overall evidence package supports an Accepted decision at Medium assurance level.",
